Subject: [PATCH 16/16] Add PAI_STATE.json producer (upstream issue #1132)

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1132

The statusline-command.sh STATE meter line reads PAI_STATE.json at
~/.claude/PAI/USER/TELOS/PAI_STATE.json. The file is never created
because:

  - ComputeGap.ts (named as the producer in the comment at
    statusline-command.sh:1149) only prints to stdout / appends to
    gap-history.jsonl. Never writes PAI_STATE.json. Covers only
    3/5 dimensions. Emits no `pct` value.
  - No cron, no launchd, no SessionStart hook, no routine invokes
    any producer.
  - `grep -rn "PAI_STATE\.json"` returns zero non-statusline refs.

Result: every user sees `STATE: HEALTH N/A | CREATIVE N/A |
FREEDOM N/A | RELATIONS N/A | FIN N/A` in their statusline. Dead
widget.

Fix (separates producer from analytics, per the upstream issue's
suggestion):

  1. Ship USER/TELOS/PAI_STATE_INPUT.yaml — user-rated pct: 0-100 |
     null per dimension. Bootstrap default is all-null so the
     statusline renders N/A until the user populates it.
  2. Ship TOOLS/WritePaiState.ts — deterministic YAML→JSON
     converter, ~50 lines. Writes the schema statusline-command.sh
     already expects (.dimensions.<dim>.pct). Validates: pct must
     be a number 0-100 or null.
  3. Wire WritePaiState.ts into a SessionStart hook chain via
     settings.json. ~10ms overhead per session start.
  4. Fix misleading comments in statusline-command.sh:1149,
     :1183-1184 to point at the new producer.

ComputeGap.ts is left alone as a report tool (its actual purpose).
The statusline contract (lines 1188-1195, tier coloring 1165-1177)
stays unchanged.

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/USER/TELOS/PAI_STATE_INPUT.yaml      NEW (12 lines)
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/TOOLS/WritePaiState.ts               NEW (51 lines, executable)
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/statusline-command.sh                :1149, 1183-1184 (comment fixes)
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/settings.json                            :SessionStart chain (add hook)

Total: 4 files (2 NEW + 2 modified), 5 hunks.

The yaml dep needed by WritePaiState.ts is already declared in the
root package.json (patch 0015) and available via bun's directory-
walking module resolution.

Co-existence: patches 0012 and 0014 modify settings.json; this
patch's hunk targets a different region (SessionStart chain).
Patches 0001-0015 do not touch statusline-command.sh.

Hunks generated against post-0015 result/ tree (for modified files)
and /dev/null (for new files). New-file mode headers inserted
manually for nix's patch -p1 compatibility.
